Package: scCanonical
Title: Analysis of Conserved and Specific Markers in Single-Cell RNA Sequencing
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Lingzhang", "Meng", email = "187398958@qq.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The scCanonical package provides tools for analyzing single-cell RNA
    sequencing data. It focuses on identifying conserved markers across clusters
    and computing specificity scores for differential expression analysis. The
    package includes functions for marker identification using Seurat, calculating
    specificity scores, and visualizing results with customizable scatter plots.
    It is designed to facilitate robust single-cell data analysis in biological
    research.
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports: Seurat (>= 4.0.0), dplyr (>= 1.0.0), ggplot2 (>= 3.3.0), ggrepel (>= 0.9.0)
Suggests: none
